One particularly grief-stricken soul caught his eye – a young woman whose child had died in a tragic accident. As she sobbed uncontrollably, Cerberus gently pawed at her knees until she looked up, surprised by the sudden attention. Then, with a soft whuff, he leaned into her and let out a gentle nudge, as if to say “Everything will be okay.” And for just a moment, it was. The woman’s tears subsided, replaced by a faint smile, and she nodded thanks to Caron before continuing on her way.
