As he stood watch over the river Styx, Caron couldn’t help but wonder – was Cerberus some kind of angel sent to ease the passage of those who left this world behind? Or was he simply a reminder that, no matter how dark things seemed, there was always hope for a brighter tomorrow? Either way, Caron knew he couldn’t ask for a better partner in the afterlife."
